<br>
If you are approached by someone who isn't roleplaying, be polite and stay in character.  If you are approached by some twit telling you how to play your character, mock them.  They will get on your nerves anyway, so may as well have some fun at thier expense.<br>
<br>
--Sset <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufrogggystyle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Frogggystyle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/17/01 7:07:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=21>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.comedycentral.com/tv_shows/southpark//images/timmy1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The use of \OOC channel</span><hr size=1> Hehe, I don't have to be forceful. But, I will explain my point of view before I bid you ado. The premise of the thread was to get a consensus from the players about the feel of roleplaying on FV, not just to advocate my point or my own experiences. And the use of the term &quot;RP Nazi&quot; was a mockery of the &quot;Soup Nazi&quot; character on Seinfeld. I was not referring to any similiarieties of the German Nazis and those who take their desires to RP in EQ too far, by my standards. It is clear, to me, with even this simple demonstration of jesting that the narrow-mindedness (RP-only or GET OUT!) on this server is going to deter anyone with a sense of real-life humor from lasting long here. This server will be dominated by hard-assed RP zealots, extremists, diehards, et al. who will demand everyone talk and act like they do. A lack of diversity and sense of individuality isn't very fun for a lot of people.<br>
<br>
The server, whether you choose to admit it or not, *IS* by every definition set up as an alignment server. Not once have you seen a comment made by Absor, Brad, or anyone else that dictated how players should roleplay. They can't because they have no way to enforce RP'ing. The server *IS* set up as an alignment server, which determines everything you can do, who you can group with, experience penalties and bonuses, who you can be buffed or rezzed by, etc. The way you RP has no concrete action against your ability to group with others, having a different alignment does. Yes, the little tag say 'Roleplaying Prefered&quot;, but that is not the process by which you have to play the game on Firiona Vie. The process is set by your alignment, which determines everything you can and can not do functionality-wise, therefore it is an alignment server. No, it is not a Zek. Yes, roleplaying is preferred. Are all players going to RP like everyone else? No. Are all players going to be restricted in their grouping by their alignment? Yes. You do the math then let me know whether or not this is an RP server or an alignment server.<br>
<br>
This commentary is all for not. I've already decided to not play on FV due to the...and yes, I'll say it...RP NAZIS that go around telling others how to play the game. I play by Verant's rules, i.e. I do not KS, I don't train intentionally, I do treat others with respect, etc. The idea of having the challenge of alignment dictate who I can and can not group with sounded interesting at first, but the player base with the incessant whining did me in. There is whining everywhere you go, true. But I really didn't feel the need to subject myself to another 50+ levels of hearing people screaming across a zone, &quot;No, you can't say SoW plz, you HAVE to say 'Might thou spare a spirit of the wolf weave of magic so that I might be able to survive in this densely packed forest wherein beasts of evil and torment live?&quot; *puke* I'll stick with, &quot;SoW plz,&quot; thanks. While RP is fun when everyone else is doing it to, it becomes too taxing for me to try and incorporate RP when everyone has their own ideology of how it should be performed. <br>
<br>
I'm not trying to be demeaning or adverse, I just wanted to express my own thoughts on the matter as lived through my own experiences in my short stint here on FV. Roleplaying isn't hard for me, as I am sure it is not for most of you. But when it boils down to it, this game is still Everquest and no matter where you go you are roleplaying character to some degree. Some do it more than others on various servers. (Felishanna is a prime example of how players can roleplay on any server.) At least here you can roleplay and be praised for it. With that, I bid you all good luck, no hard feelings, and I hope the server is all you hoped to make it. :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufelishannasecretlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felishanna Secretlight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/17/01 7:53:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The use of \OOC channel</span><hr size=1> OOC.<br>
Since you brought my name into your post Bello (Froggy's character name), I will reply.<br>
<br>
Yes, you can roleplay on any server, and yes I have shown it can be done, but you know as well as anyone the gauntlet I have had to run from anti-RP nazis, to butcher your phrase, on the standard blue server we both come from. Everything from exclusion, insults and vilification, personal harassment, lies, and even threats, to try to get the roleplayer to change to a non-roleplaying approach, even though the roleplayer for the most part keeps entirely within their own circle of friends.<br>
<br>
If this is typical of how roleplayers are treated on other servers too, can you imagine how pleased we all might be to actually get a server 'of our own'? Because this is how we feel about Firiona Vie. Some will go too far, and attack the militant non-roleplayers in the way roleplayers have ever been attacked on others. I will not condone it, but I can understand it.<br>
<br>
But Firiona Vie IS a roleplaying server. Not because Verant said it was. But because we players here will make it that way. And if this means the non-roleplayers who have come here and refuse to join in the community style get some problems from this, they also can consider why exactly they moved here. Because unlike roleplayers before Firiona Vie was launched, they have 30+ other servers to choose from.<br>
