<br>
The thing I was expecting on this server was more tolerance, not a complete swing the other way. The tag says 'Roleplay Prefered', not 'Roleplay Mandatory'. I was hoping that those who wished to roleplay would be able to do so without harassment and that those who chose not to roleplay as much as others would still be able to play in the manner they wished. Had this been a 'Roleplay STRICTLY Enforced' server, I would have nothing to say right now. But, since it is an alignment-geared server that prefers players that roleplay, I believe I still have the right to tell my side of my own experiences.<br>
<br>
In all honesty, I was really looking forward to roleplaying and playing under the confines of alignments. It just seems to make more sense. But not everyone is on the same page. I can get just as much roleplaying on Lanys as I can here, without a fraction of the bickering. And that is the reason why I chose to go back to Lanys. I am sure this server will eventually lose a majority of the d00dz along the way because they will be ostricized for their behaivor. Perhaps some time in the future I will come back to explore FV's potential to be the roleplay server most of you are hoping to make it.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukeldal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>keldal</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/17/01 10:33:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The use of \OOC channel</span><hr size=1> Felishana,<br>
